The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Board berth for Mallya son

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT 

 Siddarth

 Mumbai, May 7: Siddarth Mallya, the young Mallya scion who turned 18 today, has joined the board of United Breweries Holdings Limited (UBHL), the main holding company of the UB Group. He comes in as an additional director. Siddarth is the only son of UB Group chairman Vijay Mallya. 

 The UB Group has major holdings in McDowell Ltd, United Breweries and major stakes in the Indian subsidiary of Aventis, a pharma company. It also has huge land estates in Bangalore and is promoting Kingfisher Airlines, which is going to start its commercial operations on Monday.

 ?Siddarth will have to start from the bottom before he gets charge of any company of the UB Group,? said Vijay Mallya after taking Sidhartha on the board of the main holding company of the group.

 In addition to UBHL, Siddarth Mallya has also been appointed on the boards of three investment companies controlled by the Mallya family, which in turn are the members of the promoter group of UBHL. These companies are Mallya Private Ltd, The Gem Investment amp; Trading Company Private Limited and Kamsco Industries Private Limited. 




